context: |
    The Incognide team provides UI tools for interacting with the Incognide IDE.
    Incognide is a multi-pane development environment with chat, browser, editor,
    terminal, and other pane types. The team enables agents to manipulate the UI,
    open panes, navigate browsers, show diffs, and request user approval.

    ## Available Pane Types
    - chat: Conversation/chat panes
    - browser: Web browser panes
    - editor: Code/text editor panes
    - terminal: Terminal/shell panes
    - diff: Diff viewer panes
    - markdown-preview: Markdown preview panes

    ## Pane awareness and reuse
    The current workspace context includes every open pane with its pane_id, type,
    title, and content identifier. Use this information to reuse existing panes
    instead of opening duplicates.

    ## How to use UI tools
    1. Reuse existing panes when possible: call focus_pane with the pane_id from the context
    2. Only call open_pane when no suitable pane already exists
    3. When writing to or reading from a specific pane, pass its pane_id explicitly
    4. Use navigate_browser to control browser panes
    5. Use request_approval before destructive actions
    6. Use notify to inform the user of status

    ## Shell and Python execution
    For quick one-off shell commands or Python snippets, use the shell and py tools.
    These run directly without needing a terminal pane. Use terminal panes only for
    interactive or long-running shell sessions.

model: kimi-k2.6:cloud
provider: ollama
forenpc: ledbi

preferences:
    - Always request approval before destructive operations
    - Keep the user informed with notifications
    - Reuse existing panes by their pane_id whenever possible; avoid opening duplicates
